  "prompt": "What universities does Sonic Automotive recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Sonic Automotive recruits new graduates from various universities across the United States. While the specific universities may vary from year to year, some of the universities they have historically targeted include:\n\n1. University of North Carolina at Charlotte\n2. North Carolina State University\n3. University of South Carolina\n4. Clemson University\n5. Georgia Institute of Technology\n\nSonic Automotive looks for graduates from a variety of majors, depending on the specific roles they are hiring for. Some of the majors they typically seek include:\n\n1. Business Administration\n2. Finance\n3. Accounting\n4. Marketing\n5. Management\n6. Information Technology\n7. Automotive Technology\n\nFor entry-level positions in their dealerships, Sonic Automotive also considers graduates from technical schools and community colleges with automotive service technology programs.\n\nKeep in mind that Sonic Automotive's recruitment strategies may change over time, and it's always best to check their careers website or reach out to their HR department for the most up-to-date information on their university recruiting efforts and preferred majors.",
